A woman was seriously injured following a car crash on the M4 between La Lucia and Umhlanga on Tuesday. Netcare 911, Emer-G-Med, Durban North SAPS, KZN VIP Ambulance, Ethekwini Fire and Rescue and Marshall Security were on scene. According to Shawn Herbst of Netcare 911, reports indicate that a car and truck were involved in the crash. “The only patient, an adult female had sustained serious injuries and was treated on scene by an emergency care practitioner while the fire and rescue services used hydraulic tools to free the woman stuck in the car,” said Herbst. He added that the woman was transported by ambulance to hospital for further care.